  "prompt": "What is the difference between IIT and any renowned private college?",
  "response": "Here are key differences between IITs and renowned private colleges:\n\nIITs:\n1. Government-funded institutions\n2. Extremely competitive entrance exam (JEE Advanced)\n3. Lower fees compared to private colleges\n4. Highly standardized curriculum\n5. Strong research and academic focus\n6. Excellent placement opportunities\n7. Global recognition and reputation\n8. Mostly engineering and technical programs\n9. Strict academic discipline\n10. National-level selection process\n\nRenowned Private Colleges:\n1. Privately funded institutions\n2. Multiple entrance exam options\n3. Higher tuition fees\n4. More flexible curriculum\n5. Industry-oriented approach\n6. Good placement opportunities\n7. Varied program offerings\n8. More flexible learning environment\n9. Often have international collaborations\n10. Easier admission process\n\nCommonalities:\n- High-quality education\n- Good faculty\n- Modern infrastructure\n- Career-oriented programs\n- Focus on overall student development\n\nMajor Advantage of IITs:\n- Significantly higher brand value\n- More prestigious\n- Better research opportunities\n- Higher average placement packages\n\nMajor Advantage of Private Colleges:\n- More diverse programs\n- Less competitive admission\n- More personalized attention\n- Flexible learning environment\n\nThe choice depends on individual preferences, academic goals, and financial capabilities.",
